Noonie,<br>
<br>
You posted how many times the 2 wizards rodded, but not how many times you rodded.<br>
<br>
This is a very key variable in your parse.<br>
<br>
Since, as you say, this was a crawl with no time to sit, it plays totally into the hands of those that have good standing mana regen.  *Nobody* compares to a mage+rods+Torpor/CE(doesnt matter which, they are both accomplishing the same goal, to massivly enhange mage mana-regen with someone elses mana) for standing/moving mana-regen.<br>
<br>
On boss fights, I often have a Shaman/Cleric assigned to just heal me, and I don't sit once during the fight.  I have produced insane amounts of mana (aka Frenzied Transvergence) during some long fights while still doing excellent DPS...but I have to divide that DPS by a factor of two at the end, since it is not me, it is me + Cleric/Shaman.  Its a symbiosis; neither of us could do anywhere near that DPS seperately.  The duo is greater then the seperate parts.  In the case of Mage + Shaman 1 + 1 = 5.  Thats why its called a Force Multiplier instead of a Force Adder. An enchanter + melees does the same, while the ENC may have dismal DPS they allow melees to do far more then then either could do seperately on their own.<br>
<br>
Mistress Finraziel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujazzen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jazzen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 208<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 8:49:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: deep parse #2: wiz/wiz/mag/mnk (ok edited :P)</span><hr size=1> Bad parsing like this will cause mages to get nerfed and will cause us not to get the proper upgrades we need. I was trashed in this thread but alot of other people are now coming in to say &quot;ya this parse isn't clear&quot;. This parse isn't balanced because the group isn't balanced.  I don't need FT10 and a shaman rodding me to out damage a under-equipped lvl 58 mage. A mage with epic/bob/ft10 isn't comparable with a un-epic mage at lvl 58. Just like comparing a mage with those items to a rogue that isn't on the same lvl isn't far. Also if you are getting topor from a shaman or CH from a cleric I see no reason why a bard boosting the haste in the group 25% would be to a disadvantage to the mage? I think if you put a enchanter/bard in your group with people that are equal in equipment you will see that your damage isn't as awesome as you think. A rogue in ssra temple gear will sustain a higher dps then a mage over 2hours in a experience group even with epic. <br>
